From: Yifei Sun <ysun@hey.com>
Date: Wed Jun 3 2026 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Table export: don't pop out_limit for a never-exported old route

Effectively reverts upstream commit 682d83ea ("Table export: Drop redundant
not-seen old route nullification"), forward-ported past the later refactor
34a8a274 ("Table: Optimal and Any Export refactoring") so it applies to the
current rt_notify_basic().

---
 nest/rt-table.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/nest/rt-table.c b/nest/rt-table.c
--- a/nest/rt-table.c
+++ b/nest/rt-table.c
@@ -1431,6 +1431,10 @@ rt_notify_basic(struct channel *c, const rte *new, const rte *old, const rte *trt
       /* Treat old rejected as never seen. */
       old = NULL;
     }
+    else if (!bmap_test(&c->export_accepted_map, old->id))
+      /* In neither map => never exported on this channel, so do_rt_notify()
+       * must not pop out_limit for it (would underflow: limit.h:35). */
+      old = NULL;

     /* Accepted bit is dropped in do_rt_notify() */
   }
